narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: As an international student, during this coarse I was able to gain a great knowledge on complex societies around the world.
I enjoyed learning about the theoretical framework that shaped the way archaeologists have studied complexity. Also learned a bit about the best approaches to doing comparative studies.
The course provided an broad and comprehensive overview to complex societies around the globe. It is an ideal starting point for a graduate student in an archaeological studies program.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The professionals who are engaged with some of the topics of the coarse were involved, which provides a substantial insights.
A lot of lecture. It would be nice to give a little bit more time to class discussion, but I enjoyed the lectures so this isn't much of a complaint.
Strengths: Expertise of professors and guest speakers Quality and diversity of assigned readings

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Every archaeology graduate students should take this coarse! Strongly recommend.
Yes. Co-taught courses are very interesting because of the perspectives brought in by each instructor.
I would recommend this course highly to any student interested in anthropology or archaeology.
